description:
secretx-keyring/src/lib.rs has tests for `from_uri_empty_account` (line 240-247) and `from_uri_empty_path` (line 249-256) but no test for `from_uri_empty_service`. The sibling crate secretx-desktop has this exact test (secretx-desktop/src/lib.rs:224-230, name `from_uri_empty_service`, asserts that `secretx:desktop:/account` returns `InvalidUri`).

The empty-service code path IS implemented at secretx-keyring/src/lib.rs:81-85:
```rust
if service.is_empty() {
    return Err(SecretError::InvalidUri(
        "keyring URI: service name must not be empty".into(),
    ));
}
```

…but there is no test verifying it. A regression that accidentally accepts an empty service (e.g., a refactor that reorders the validation) would silently break this invariant and forward an empty service string to `keyring::Entry::new("", &account)` — which keyring would then reject with a less-actionable error.

Trigger: a contributor refactors `from_uri` (e.g. rewrites the service/account split) and breaks the empty-service guard.

Resolution: copy the test from secretx-desktop verbatim with backend name `keyring`. Trivial — 7 lines.
